Unless you live in a huge city like LA  New York City  Miami  etc. your Tinder experience will no longer be the same as it was a few years ago. Now there are more bot accounts that I run into than actual people. And they're easy to spot; they usually have only four pictures  they are either a ""student "" ""studying at student "" go to ""New York University "" or some random university from a major US city. It feels like Tinder is scraping the internet for pictures of attractive people and purposely generating bot accounts to make you think the userbase is large and active  when it's now the opposite. Spending money on this app would be a joke  again  unless you live in a major city. If you live in a more rural area  you can forget about it. Stick to going out and meeting people. I'm sorry Tinder  but unless you come up with some unique form of profile verification  or admit that you're botting your own userbase  I have reason to believe you're on the quick decline into becoming irrelevant.

If you're a non-judgemental guy like me  you're just going to be mindlessly swiping to the right most of the time and waiting for a like. That's not a bad thing - the Tinder model is mindless  but that's how it should be for dating apps  and it is far superior to the likes of OKCupid and Plenty of Fish  which ask all sorts of pointless personal questions under the pseudo-scientific justification they can find you better matches. A couple of points to note with this app - there are a lot of fake profiles on Tinder by spambots  and you should never respond to anyone's profile that asks you to contact them on something like Kik. They're usually trying to scam you or make you register for something. Edit 12/04/2017: downvoting to 3 stars due to a massive wave of spam and fake profiles trying to scam you. Given you have only limited likes a day  this is pretty unacceptable  and Tinder needs to do more to clean up its profiles.

TL;DR: It's great  and it's fun  but I'd recommend downloading OkCupid as well.
